Key Match Events: Australia won the match to reach the T20 World Cup final.
Matthew Wade hit three sixes in a row to seal the win.
Matthew Wade scored 41 not out from 17 balls.
Marcus Stoinis scored 40 not out from 31 balls.
David Warner scored 49 runs from 30 balls.
Shadab Khan took 4 wickets for 26 runs.
Pakistan scored 176-4 with Rizwan scoring 67 runs from 52 balls and Fakhar scoring 55 not out from 32 balls.
Mitchell Starc took 2 wickets for 38 runs.
Post-Match Reflections: Aaron Finch acknowledged the team's sloppiness but praised the depth of the team.
Matthew Wade expressed happiness for contributing to the win and repaying the faith after being out of the team.
Aatif Nawaz noted Pakistan's disappointment despite their strong performance throughout the tournament.
Carlos Brathwaite highlighted the fine margins and the impact of Hassan Ali's missed opportunity.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia will face New Zealand in the final.
The match was held in Dubai.
